post_text:
WE NEED YOU!

Avoca Central School is working on our strategic plan and needs your feedback. It only takes a minute to offer your thoughts and to see what everyone else is thinking.

Please tell us what you think we are doing well and what we can improve on. We would also like to know what you think we should be considering for the future. Our plans will be based on your feedback. Please share your thoughts through 6/30 by clicking on the following link to a thought exchange: https://my.thoughtexchange.com/113321331

You can add thoughts, see what other community members are thinking and rate each other‚Äôs feedback. All of this is done anonymously, and we encourage you to check back often to keep the conversation going. The exchange will be open until June 30th. Over the coming months, the board and leadership team will be using your feedback for discussions and planning with volunteers from all groups in our school community. Stay tuned for more information on how to get involved further.

Thanks again for your support and feedback!

Stephen Saxton
Superintendent of Schools

Budget vote update: Absentee ballots now accepted by mail through June 16

An Executive Order by Governor Andrew Cuomo issued on June 7 has extended the deadline for school districts to receive mailed-in absentee ballots to June 16. The order does not affect the deadline of hand-delivered ballots.

To be counted, school budget ballots can be accepted by hand delivery through 5 p.m. on June 9, and received by mail through June 16 by the school district.

Absentee ballot deadlines by delivery method

Hand-delivery to the district office ‚Äî Tuesday, June 9, by 5 p.m.

Mail-in and delivery by USPS courier ‚Äî Tuesday, June 16

To learn more about voting by absentee ballot and the 2020-21 proposed budget visit https://www.avocacsd.org/Page/1438

Steuben County Public Health
May 29 at 11:54 AM ¬∑

The Southern Tier Region, which includes Steuben County, has met all the required metrics established by the Governor's Office, and Steuben County, NY supports Phase 2 businesses which include:
- Office-based work
- Hair salons and barber shops
- Real estate
- Commercial building management
- Retail - essential and in store sales
- Vehicle sales, leases and rentals
- Retail rental, repair and cleaning

Guidance for Phase 2 businesses can be found at https://forward.ny.gov/phase-two-industries.

See the press release included for statements from the Steuben County Legislative Chairman and the County Manager.

Attention District Voters:
Absentee Ballots for the June 9th school budget vote and election have been mailed to all registered voters of the Avoca Central School District. Reminder absentee ballots are the only method to vote this year.

The District Budget Newsletter will be mailed on May 28, after the Budget Hearing, to all residences in the school district. Please wait for this information before you vote. Please also remind your neighbors and family to wait for the budget newsletter before voting.

If you did not receive an absentee ballot and would like one (and you are a qualified voter of the Avoca School District) please call Rosalie Smith 607-566-3000 ext. 1110 or email rsmith@avocacsd.org.

Thank you

Dear Avoca Families and Community,

As we near six weeks into the Covid-19 school closures, teachers, students and families alike are determined to make the most of the alternative distance learning environment while navigating a myriad of concurrent challenges.

More than ever, it will take every one of us to provide our students with the best possible learning experience while we adapt to new ways of delivering instruction and engaging with one another.

That‚Äôs why we want to hear from you. Please share your thoughts and ideas with us on ThoughtExchange, an online tool for public engagement in leadership. Go to https://my.thoughtexchange.com/288041433 answer the question, and return later to rate other responses to the same topic. We will use this information to improve learning tools and supports, as we continue to adapt to the remote environment.

Thank you for participating. Your experience matters.atters.

If you or someone you know has been affected financially by COVID-19, WIC may be able to help. WIC (The Special Supplemental Nutrition Program for Women, Infants, and Children) provides pregnant women, new and breastfeeding moms, and children under age 5 with healthy food, breastfeeding support, nutrition advice, and referrals to other services.
Steuben and Yates County residents are encouraged to reach out to our WIC Help Specialist, Amanda, either by text/call: (607)-377-4313 or via email at: DowdleA@proactioninc.org for more information or to find out if they may be eligible.
Visit our website: www.proactioninc.org for more on all programs and services at ProAction of Steuben and Yates, Inc.

NOTICE: New York state school budget votes and board of education elections will be delayed until at least June 1, 2020, according to an executive order released by Governor Andrew Cuomo on Monday, March 30, 2020.

The order specifically says, ‚ÄúAny school board, library board, or village election scheduled to take place in April or May of 2020 is hereby postponed until at least June 1, 2020, and subject to further directive as to the timing, location or manner of voting for such elections.‚Äù

This change will also impact school districts‚Äô regular notification practices and timelines for sharing information about the vote and election.

NY Governor Andrew Cuomo today announced that all schools across New York State will remain closed an additional two weeks, extending the closure to April 15, 2020, in order to protect students and staff from the spread of Covid-19 Coronavirus. Additionally the Governor said this date would be reevaluated as we get closer to April 15.
The Governor had initially ordered all schools in the state to close for two weeks beginning on March 16, 2020.

Wednesday's boys basketball game:

Admission is $5, there will be two admission tables (at each entrance of the gym), and you can go to either.

WABH is covering the game, so you can listen by:
tuning your radio to either 100.3FM or 1380AM
streaming from their website
downloading the "TuneIn" app and searching for "WABH" and streaming from any enabled device
If our boys win, they will play Sherman (from Section VI) at Buffalo State College at 12PM on Sat, 03/14.

shared_text:
Steuben County Historical Society
December 19, 2019 at 8:01 AM ¬∑

This photo is one from a set of four that had us puzzled for quite a while. A couple of board members suggested that it might be the old Presbyterian church in Avoca, which turned out to be wrong, but it DID lead us to the RIGHT identification... this is the old BAPTIST church in Avoca. The bell being removed now stands in front of Avoca First Baptist. There are also large bells "on exhibit" at Bath Fire Hall; Canisteo Fire Hall; Curtiss Musuem (from the old Hammondsport Academy); Bath Centenary Methodist Church; St. Mary Church in Rexville; and, we believe, Hartsville Community Church. Any others in Steuben County?
